## Types of permissions for files and folders (To view permission, right-click and then click properties, and then security)
Read (folder) - allows viewing and listening to files and subfolders 
Read (file) - allows viewing or accessing a file's contents 
Write (folder) - permits adding of files and subfolders
Write (file) - permits writing a file
Read and Execute (folder and file) - Same as read, but you can now execute 
Listen Folder Contents (folder only) - allows listening and viewing of files and subfolders as well as executing, but for subfolders only. 
Modify (folder and file) - Allows read, write, and now deletion of the file and folder
Full Control (folder and file) - allows read, write, deletion, and changing of a folder or file  

## Administrator
To see if you are an administrator, go to other users and see if you have an add button. 
Using the run app and then lusrmgr.msc (Local User and Group Management) allows you to see all of the users
